  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know you're over your relationship?",
  "response": "Recognizing that you\u2019re over a relationship can be a complex emotional process. Here are some signs that may indicate you\u2019ve moved on:\n\n1. **Emotional Detachment**: You no longer feel a strong emotional connection or attachment to your partner. Thoughts of them don\u2019t evoke strong feelings of sadness or anger.\n\n2. **No Longer Idealizing**: You\u2019re able to see your partner clearly, recognizing both their strengths and weaknesses without placing them on a pedestal or reminiscing about the relationship fondly.\n\n3. **Less Frequent Thoughts**: You find that you think about your ex less often, or when you do, it\u2019s not accompanied by a sense of longing or regret.\n\n4. **Interest in New Experiences**: You feel open to meeting new people, exploring new relationships, or trying new activities without significant hesitation or feelings of guilt.\n\n5. **Acceptance of the Past**: You\u2019ve come to terms with the end of the relationship and have accepted that it\u2019s over, rather than longing for what once was.\n\n6. **Focus on Self**: You feel more focused on your personal growth, interests, and happiness, rather than being hindered by the past relationship.\n\n7. **Positive Outlook**: You have a hopeful outlook on future relationships and are excited about the possibilities rather than fearing being hurt again.\n\n8. **Support From Friends and Family**: Your support system recognizes that you\u2019ve moved on and encourages you to embrace new beginnings.\n\n9. **Reduced Grievances**: You no longer feel the need to talk about your ex or the relationship with friends or family, indicating that you\u2019ve processed those feelings.\n\n10. **Personal Fulfillment**: You\u2019re finding fulfillment and happiness in your life independently, rather than feeling incomplete without your ex.\n\nIf you find many of these resonate with you, it may be a good indication that you\u2019ve moved on. It\u2019s important to be patient with yourself throughout this process, as healing can take time.",
